Reindex requests support a "size" parameter under the "source" parameter, like so:
```
{
  "source": {
    "remote": {
      "host": "http://otherhost:9200",
      "username": "user",
      "password": "pass"
    },
    "index": "source",
    "size": 10
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "dest"
  }
}
```
However, curator does not: https://github.com/elastic/curator/blob/v5.1.2/curator/defaults/option_defaults.py#L156

This affects the batch size that documents from "source" are processed in and is different from the "size" parameter in the root of the body which caps the number of documents that will be reindexed.  Both parameters are included in examples in the [documentation](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/5.0/docs-reindex.html)

